        { "en": "He must be tired → debe de estar cansado.", "es": "[locked]" },
        { "en": "You usually arrive early → sueles llegar temprano.", "es": "[locked]" }
      ],
      "cue": "Spanish modals fine-tune intention—grammar that balances how sure, soft, or hopeful a statement feels."
    },
    {
      "phase": "rest",
      "line": "Spanish gives even small verbs emotional gravity. Each *puede que* or *debería* carries more than logic—it carries how deeply the speaker believes what they say."
    }
